<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880531-0185 </DOCNO><HL> Notable andamp; Quotable </HL><SO> </SO><TEXT>      Economist Peter T. Bauer, writing in the National Chamber Foundation's Journal of Economic Growth:   The Third World as an aggregate is the creation of foreign aid. Without aid, there is no such collectivity as the Third World, or South. Foreign aid is therefore the source of the North-South conflict, not its solution. </TEXT></DOC>